The business news network CNBC on Wednesday <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2025/04/02/cnbc-makes-debut-on-apple-tv-and-roku.html">announced</a> that its CNBC+ streaming service has expanded to the Apple TV and Roku devices.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/04/CNBC-Apple-TV-App.jpeg" alt="" width="1286" height="723" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-997573" /><br/>
CNBC+ is now available through the <a href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/cnbc-stock-market-business/id398018310">CNBC app</a> on all Apple TV HD and Apple TV 4K models, providing subscribers with a live stream of the CNBC channel, along with full episodes of popular CNBC shows on demand. In the App Store, a subscription to CNBC+ in the U.S. costs &#36;14.99 per month, or &#36;149.99 per year.<br/>
<br/>
The streaming service first launched in late 2024 on iOS, Android, and CNBC.com, according to a CNBC spokesperson.<div class="linkback">Related Roundup: <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/apple-tv/">Apple TV</a></div><div class="linkback">Tag: <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/cnbc-com/">CNBC</a></div><div class="linkback">Buyer's Guide: <a href="https://buyersguide.macrumors.com/#Apple_TV">Apple TV (Don't Buy)</a></div><div class="linkback">Related Forum: <a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/forums/apple-tv-and-home-theater.100">Apple TV and Home Theater</a></div><br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/04/03/cnbc-plus-on-apple-tv/">CNBC+ Now Available on Apple TV</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/cnbc-now-available-on-apple-tv.2454600/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>